CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 14, 1967, pg. 2B reads: "Mr. and Mrs. Michael Seale - Harris Photo." Portion of Accompanying article reads: "Howard U. Grands Repeat Vows in Pittsburgh Rites - A romance that began in college, culminated at the altar for lovely Junyetta Jelks and Michael Cecil Asquith Seale.  The couple repeated nuptial vows during a double ring ceremony recently at Trinity AME Church here in Pittsburgh with Father Henderson officiating. The bride is the daughter of Mrs. Juanita Jelks of Morgan St. The groom is the son of Cecil A. Seale of Brooklyn, M.Y.
TitMainTitle: Bride Junyetta Jelks Seale and Groom Michael Cecil Asquith Seale, walking down aisle of Trinity AME Church
